  <static seed="64" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/FractionArithmetic/AddFractions30.pg">
    <statement><p>Add: <m>\displaystyle{-\frac{2}{5} + \frac{3}{5}}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{1}{5}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To add two fractions with the same denominator, we simply add up the numerators and keep the denominator unchanged.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}[t]
   -\frac{2}{5} + \frac{3}{5}
        \amp = \frac{-2 + 3}{5} \\
        \amp = \frac{1}{5}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The answer is  <m>\displaystyle{\frac{1}{5}}</m>.</p>
</solution>
